Vehnn
</FONT></TD>
<TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">You can left click off any of your own buffs, not including say a dot you casted on yourself.  You can also click off many utility buffs cast on you by another person, like levitate, see invis, sow, etc.  Trying to click off a hp/stat buff cast on you by someone else will give you a "you cannot remove this effect" message.<P>The level 12 "memory blur" spell completely wipes the hate list of a mob when successful.  It's very reliable up to around level 35 monsters, as long as the target is not way red to you.  The best use of it is say your puller brings two mobs, and you mez the extra, and then tash and slow it.  The mob will be very upset with you when mez breaks, but if you blur it it will forget all about you (and anyone else until they attack it or it's naturally KOS).<P>The lull line of spells don't work that way.  They don't have anything to do with the hate list a monster currently has.  What they do is, say you have 2 mobs of the same type next to each other.  Normally if you attacked one the other would see that and attack as well.  On a successful cast, the mob you casted on basically becomes blind - it will not attack you as well if it's friend is attacked.  Of course if its resisted both mobs will aggro.  Why this line of spells was given to the class that needs it the least is anyone's guess.<P>About hide - as a DE myself I find I get around 30% success rate on it, which isn't bad.  I assume that if you cast illusion dark elf you would get the hide ability in your ability box the way you get slam from ogre and troll illusions.</FONT>
</TD></TR>

